orkable. Another idea</span><hr size=1> I love Karak's idea.  You would have to allot inventory room for the various poisons you want around, but it couldn't possibly be worse than the 2 10-slot containers I expend on poison in its current form.  I don't even think it needs to be as restrictive as he wants to make it.<br>
<br>
Why?  Because with Endless Quiver and various other AA skills, a ranger can do 500-700 damage per arrow WITHOUT the trueshot disc supposedly -- and the fancy arrow needed doesn't even get expended.<br>
<br>
Some high end guilds are actually *recruiting* rangers with these skills -- rangers, the long time "only level 61 rangers need apply", being actively recruited!<br>
<br>
Our AA skills in current form are a big yawn.  Things like Double Riposte (helloooooooo, im a rogue, im not supposed to get hit!) and Purge Poison do nothing to increase Rogue usefulness or even give us "roleplayish" roguely skills fitting with the class.<br>
<br>
This would be a skill worthy of the rogue.  If there is concern over its power, make it expensive and give it more pre-requisistes. Add another class skill "Advanced poison mastery",  which would decrease the chance to fail on making poison by another 25%, 12 points, that has it own pre-requisite of poison mastery 3.  <br>
<br>
So in order to get Everful Poison you would need 6 general points, 12 archetype points, 18 points in Poison Mastery, 12 points in Advanced Poison Mastery, and then 12 points for Everful Poison itself.<br>
<br>
That would make sixty points a person would need.  Thats a LOT of points.<br>
<br>
Or, instead of creating the extra pre-requisite, make Everful Poison a graded skill of 3, 6, 9 points - at level 1, you have a 25% chance of not expending the poison, at level 2, a 50% chance, and at level 3 you have a 99% chance.<br>
<br>
In one fell swoop I would suddenly have a goal that would make my 250 skill mean something! <p><font color="#FFFFCC"><b><font face="Bradley Hand ITC">Shalara & Shalysa De'Tan</font></b><font face="Bradley Hand ITC" size="2">
